{"word":"ἐπιθύω","slug":"ἐπιθύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπιθύω1</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:θύω'><el>θύω1</el></a> I. 3\n<el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ύσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to sacrifice besides</i> or <i>after</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to offer incense on</i> the altar; generally <i>to offer</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div> <hr/> <el><b>ἐπιθύω2</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:θύω'><el>θύω2</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a>,\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to rush eagerly at</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to strive vehemently to</i> do a thing, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b>Hhymn.</b><p/></div><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἐπῑ-θύ¯ω</el> in <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>\n"}]}